This paper is about a new algorithm for semi-supervised learning that achieves state-of-the-art results on multiple datasets. The algorithm involves data augmentation, label guessing, and mixing labeled and unlabeled data. These techniques are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks, which suggests that these sub-categories are likely. Additionally, the paper focuses on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques, which further supports these sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses datasets and metrics commonly used in machine learning research, which suggests that the data science (cs.DS) sub-category is also likely.
